{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17471762","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17471762"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T21:51:17+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T21:51:17+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"685"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"685","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/685"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.08,0.1,0.02,0.78,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"685"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"31244"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"685","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/685"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"685"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"17098"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"9"},{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"476"},{"type":"tags","id":"926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4578"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4988"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"9600"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"7819"},{"type":"contributions","id":"7872"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38306"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42128"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44032"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"31244","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/31244"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 14-year-old boy presents to the emergency department with progressive left sided abdominal pain. This started about two hours ago when he fell off his bicycle and landed on his left side. He is otherwise in good health, apart from a sore throat three weeks ago. On examination his blood pressure is 110/74 mmHg, pulse 98/min and temperature 37.2\u003Csup\u003Eo\u003C/sup\u003EC. There is widespread abdominal tenderness and localised tenderness over his lower left ribs when they are compressed. A bedside ultrasound shows a trace of free fluid in the pelvis.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Fractured ribs","Retroperitoneal bleed","Small bowel perforation","Rupture of the spleen","Renal haematoma"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most probable diagnosis is an injury to the spleen and \u003Cstrong\u003Esplenic rupture. \u003C/strong\u003EThe nature of his injury and the presence of abdominal and rib tenderness would support this diagnosis. The patient also has a history of sore throat which could be consistent with infectious mononucleosis which might have led to splenomegaly, thereby making the spleen more susceptible to traumatic rupture. The presence of free fluid in the pelvis supports this diagnosis by indicating that there is an extravasation of fluid (blood) from somewhere in the abdomen.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFractured ribs\u003C/strong\u003E could be a diagnosis in this case because of the presence of tenderness in the lower ribs area but more signs of respiratory difficulty, crepitus, chest wall deformity and paradoxical chest movements with a flail chest might have been expected.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Eretroperitoneal bleed\u003C/strong\u003E would be difficult to diagnose with ultrasound because of the lack of visualisation of the retroperitoneal area. It can present with abdominal tenderness but the patient will most probably be hypotensive and tachycardiac.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESmall bowel perforation\u003C/strong\u003E after road accidents is well recognised, but the nature of the event to produce such an injury is usually one of rapid deceleration or sudden compression (seat belt injury).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Erenal haematoma\u003C/strong\u003E will present as usually pain or tenderness in the flank or back region. Being a retroperitoneal structure, it would be unusual for a renal injury to lead to extravasation of blood into the peritoneal cavity (as seen on the ultrasound scan).\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Left sided localised tenderness after abdominal trauma can be a sign of splenic rupture.","In patients with abdminal trauma, a bedside FAST (Focussed abdominal scan for trauma) scan is an useful aid in diagnosis."],"references":["Akoury T, Whetstone DR. Splenic Rupture. [Updated 2022 Jul 18]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2022 Jan-.","Kuo K, Kim AM. Rib Fracture. [Updated 2022 Aug 8]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2022 Jan-.","Savatmongkorngul S, Wongwaisayawan S, Kaewlai R. Focused assessment with sonography for trauma: current perspectives. Open Access Emerg Med. 2017;9:57-62"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"17098"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"685"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"17098","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/17098"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2023-01-03T06:37:02+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-09T14:39:12+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"685"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"31244"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"9","links":{"self":"https://app.em